package for its chip industry, as Reuters exclusively reported ( https://ww=
w.reuters.com/technology/china-plans-over-143-bln-push-boost-domestic-chips=
-compete-with-us-sources-2022-12-13/ ) on Tuesday, said TechInsights=E2=80=
=99 chip economist Dan Hutcheson=E2=80=A6

With U.S. export controls making it impossible to produce advanced chips, S=
MIC is doubling down on mature technology chips and has announced four new =
facilities, or fabs, since 2020. When those come online, it would more than=
 triple the company=E2=80=99s output, estimates Samuel Wang, Gartner chip a=
nalyst. He said there is a huge ramp up in new chip fabs across China. =E2=
=80=9CAll this will start to have an impact from early 2024 and will be ful=
l blown by 2027,=E2=80=9D said Wang, adding the chip supply increase will p=
ut downward pressure on chip prices. The importance of older chip technolog=
y hit the industry in the face in 2021 as a shortage of those chips prevent=
ed manufacturing of millions of cars and consumer electronics.

This is both very smart of SMIC and China and a big problem for the U.S. fo=
r the reasons I laid out earlier this year in Chips and China ( https://str=
atechery.com/2022/chips-and-china/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZ=
CI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdWQiOiJzdHJ=
hdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJlbnQiOnsidXJpIjpbImh0dHBzOi8vc3RyYXRlY2=
